01:16:07,996 --> 01:16:12,301
And that's exactly what
Judaism wants us to do.

944
01:16:13,936 --> 01:16:18,540
The person in need is summoned to pray.

945
01:16:18,540 --> 01:16:21,843
And halachically, I could prove it
to you, but I have no time for that.

946
01:16:21,843 --> 01:16:24,046
Prayer and tzarah.

947
01:16:24,046 --> 01:16:25,681
you know what tzarah is, I mean?

948
01:16:26,181 --> 01:16:32,154
Either you say it in Sephardic
dialect or in Ashkenazic

949
01:16:32,154 --> 01:16:33,755
dialect, it's the same tzarah.

950
01:16:40,596 --> 01:16:47,069
Prayer is inseparably linked
up, bound up with tzarah.

951
01:16:47,069 --> 01:16:48,837
Who prays?

952
01:16:48,837 --> 01:16:50,973
He who is in distress.

953
01:16:54,743 --> 01:17:01,116
"Min ha'meitzar karasi Kah," out
of the narrow straits I invoke God.

954
01:17:01,550 --> 01:17:07,322
"Mi'maamakim kerasicha Adoshem,"
I invoke God de profundis,

955
01:17:07,556 --> 01:17:10,792
from the depths in which I find myself.

956
01:17:10,792 --> 01:17:14,663
"V'chi savo milchamah b'artzechem al ha'tzaar ha'tzorer es'chem,"

957
01:17:14,663 --> 01:17:17,532
when we're at war with them,

958
01:17:17,532 --> 01:17:19,067
then pray.

959
01:17:20,836 --> 01:17:27,643
And this is true according to
Maimonides as well, and Nachmanides,

960
01:17:27,643 --> 01:17:30,779
who dealt with the problem of
prayer from a halachic viewpoint.

961
01:17:30,779 --> 01:17:35,550
Prayer and need are inseparably bound up.

962
01:17:37,419 --> 01:17:46,194
If man does not experience min ha'meitzar,
narrowness, existential narrowness, if

963
01:17:46,194 --> 01:17:53,402
man is not in distress, min ha'meitzar,
if he's not somewhere in subterranean

964
01:17:53,402 --> 01:18:01,076
depths, if he feels happy and contented,
there is halachically no need for prayer.

965
01:18:01,443 --> 01:18:02,911
Doesn't have to join a temple or

966
01:18:02,911 --> 01:18:07,916
synagogue, and can save a few dollars.

967
01:18:11,186 --> 01:18:13,321
If man is happy,

968
01:18:14,523 --> 01:18:21,997
contented, prayer not only is not
necessary but it's an absurdity.

969
01:18:22,931 --> 01:18:29,104
Prayer is the result of this
consciousness, of a permanent crisis

970
01:18:29,104 --> 01:18:35,310
consciousness, the consciousness
of dolorem ferre ergo sum.

971
01:18:35,310 --> 01:18:37,312
This is prayer.

972
01:18:40,982 --> 01:18:42,751
Of course, with

973
01:18:42,751 --> 01:18:45,754
the awakening of the "need"
awareness , prayer is dependent

974
01:18:45,754 --> 01:18:47,422
upon the "need" awareness.

975
01:18:47,422 --> 01:18:51,993
If a man has a "need" awareness, then pray, ask, demand, request.

976
01:18:51,993 --> 01:18:52,627
If you have

977
01:18:52,627 --> 01:18:56,064
no "need" awareness, either your
needs are few, or you think you

978
01:18:56,064 --> 01:18:59,668
have gratified all your needs,
then there is no need for prayer.

979
01:19:00,969 --> 01:19:05,941
With the awakening of the "need"
awareness, prayer makes its entry.

980
01:19:07,342 --> 01:19:13,248
Prayer at this stage -- and I would ask
for your attention -- at this stage,

981
01:19:13,248 --> 01:19:20,122
is called tzaakah, Tzaddi-Ayin-Kuf-Hei,
tzaakah, not tefillah yet.

982
01:19:20,122 --> 01:19:21,356
Not tefillah yet.

983
01:19:21,356 --> 01:19:22,624
Tefillah is a higher word.

984
01:19:22,624 --> 01:19:24,226
I'll explain what tefillah is.

985
01:19:24,226 --> 01:19:29,030
Tzaakah, Tzaddi-Ayin-Kuf-Hei,
what does tzaakah mean in Hebrew?

986
01:19:29,698 --> 01:19:32,367
Shriek, outcry.

987
01:19:33,635 --> 01:19:38,974
And one of the attributes of the
Almighty is Shomei'a Kol Tzaakah.

988
01:19:38,974 --> 01:19:45,747
He hearkens to the voice, to the cry,

989
01:19:45,747 --> 01:19:47,916
to the shriek, to the howl.

990
01:19:49,050 --> 01:19:50,719
He hearkens to it.

991
01:19:51,153 --> 01:19:53,688
Not word, kol tzaakah.

992
01:19:54,022 --> 01:19:55,657
You don't say Shomei'a Kol Tefillah.

993
01:19:55,657 --> 01:20:01,296
You don't say it because when God hearkens
to tefillah, then He hearkens to words.

994
01:20:01,296 --> 01:20:04,366
But when it is about tzaakah,
there are no words yet.

995
01:20:04,366 --> 01:20:07,068
Man hasn't discovered the logos of need.

996
01:20:07,068 --> 01:20:11,239
He just discovered the awareness
of need, that he is a being

997
01:20:11,239 --> 01:20:12,073
in need.

998
01:20:12,073 --> 01:20:20,949
He is dependent, and the consummation of
the ideal of man, of his life – I mean,

999
01:20:20,949 --> 01:20:26,221
the meaningfulness – can only be obtained
from somewhere else, not from within.

1000
01:20:26,521 --> 01:20:29,558
Then, prayer is indispensable.

1001
01:20:29,558 --> 01:20:31,993
But this is the logos.

1002
01:20:33,228 --> 01:20:39,034
For the time being, it is
just tzaakah, just an outcry.

1003
01:20:40,001 --> 01:20:46,074
There is as yet no word, no
sentence, even though the

1004
01:20:46,074 --> 01:20:48,276
emotional awareness has awakened.

1005
01:20:49,077 --> 01:20:54,082
The logos of need is
still dormant, silent.

1006
01:20:54,549 --> 01:21:00,822
There is, as yet, no clear
understanding of what one is crying for.

1007
01:21:00,822 --> 01:21:06,094
There is, however, distress
and loud human weeping.

1008
01:21:09,064 --> 01:21:12,167
Tzaakah is primordial prayer.

1009
01:21:13,468 --> 01:21:17,906
The voice is restored;
the word is still missing.

1010
01:21:17,906 --> 01:21:21,376
He prays because he's in narrow straits.

1011
01:21:21,376 --> 01:21:23,211
He prays because

1012
01:21:23,211 --> 01:21:24,779
he is in the depths.

1013
01:21:24,779 --> 01:21:27,782
But for what he prays, he doesn't know.

1014
01:21:27,782 --> 01:21:32,020
Did our ancestors in Egypt know
when they began to pray for what?

1015
01:21:33,622 --> 01:21:38,293
Prayer was an expression of protest
against reality, against the present.

1016
01:21:40,495 --> 01:21:41,529
But what?

1017
01:21:41,529 --> 01:21:43,632
How it should be changed?

1018
01:21:43,632 --> 01:21:44,566
What man wants?

1019
01:21:44,566 --> 01:21:47,469
At this stage, he doesn't know as yet.

1020
01:21:48,970 --> 01:21:52,874
Interesting is, I mean, just as this
is a parenthetical statement, that

1021
01:21:52,874 --> 01:21:59,514
the service of Selichot, I mean, the
original service of Selichot, actually

1022
01:21:59,514 --> 01:22:01,850
represents not tefillah but tzaakah.

1023
01:22:02,851 --> 01:22:04,486
Short sentences.

1024
01:22:04,486 --> 01:22:08,556
"Ana Adoshem hoshi'ah na."
Aneinu, aneinu, aneinu, you

1025
01:22:08,556 --> 01:22:09,891
just repeat one word.

1026
01:22:09,891 --> 01:22:12,661
Aneinu, answer, hearken,
aneinu, aneinu, aneinu.

1027
01:22:13,862 --> 01:22:16,665
Later, it was elaborated and,
of course, transformed into

1028
01:22:17,065 --> 01:22:22,971
literary creations, but at the
beginning, it was just an outcry, a

1029
01:22:22,971 --> 01:22:27,709
shriek, a word whose meaning, I mean,
the worshipper did not understand.

1030
01:22:28,476 --> 01:22:34,149
Aneinu, mi sh'anah l'Avraham Avinu
b'Har Hamoriah, aneinu, ateret libi.

1031
01:22:34,149 --> 01:22:41,189
The shaliach tzibbur, the cantor, used to
say the sentence, the crowd couldn't read.

1032
01:22:41,189 --> 01:22:43,291
They didn't know how to
formulate the prayer.

1033
01:22:43,558 --> 01:22:49,064
They just answered in monosyllables
or just with one word.

1034
01:22:49,064 --> 01:22:52,300
Aneinu, hoshana, hoshana, hoshana.

1035
01:22:52,801 --> 01:22:55,270
This is the stage of tzaakah.

1036
01:22:55,704 --> 01:22:57,105
A "need" awareness has

1037
01:22:57,105 --> 01:22:58,440
awakened.

1038
01:22:59,307 --> 01:23:06,147
Man feels reality has to
be corrected, changed.

1039
01:23:06,548 --> 01:23:10,385
Man registers protest

1040
01:23:10,385 --> 01:23:12,654
against reality, but

1041
01:23:12,654 --> 01:23:16,658
he doesn't know what the substitute is.

1042
01:23:17,225 --> 01:23:18,660
This is tzaakah.

1043
01:23:20,562 --> 01:23:21,629
Let us continue.

1044
01:23:21,629 --> 01:23:22,897
Now, we come to tefillah.

1045
01:23:22,897 --> 01:23:25,734
Let us continue with our analysis.

1046
01:23:26,468 --> 01:23:32,340
There is an inner contradiction
within the "need" awareness.

1047
01:23:33,074 --> 01:23:37,746
I know my own opinion, I mean,
I've spoken so much about it

1048
01:23:38,079 --> 01:23:40,015
and I mentioned it in my essay.

1049
01:23:40,548 --> 01:23:44,586
The awareness of need is a
dialectical awareness, basically.

1050
01:23:44,919 --> 01:23:45,920
It means it has

1051
01:23:45,920 --> 01:23:47,522
an inner contradiction.

1052
01:23:48,957 --> 01:23:55,397
On the one hand, it urges man, as I stated
before, to gratify his needs and warns

1053
01:23:55,397 --> 01:23:58,299
him against any attempt to suppress them,

1054
01:23:58,666 --> 01:24:02,904
since non-gratification is
contrary to human dignity.

1055
01:24:03,271 --> 01:24:04,372
You see?

1056
01:24:04,672 --> 01:24:09,377
The first aspect of the awareness
of need is not only just that I

1057
01:24:09,377 --> 01:24:11,679
am in need: a statement of fact.

1058
01:24:11,679 --> 01:24:14,783
But there is a normative
element, a normative aspect.

1059
01:24:15,283 --> 01:24:16,484
Gratify.

1060
01:24:16,484 --> 01:24:17,752
Try to gratify your needs.

1061
01:24:18,186 --> 01:24:23,892
Don't suppress them because suppression
of needs and the denial of gratification

1062
01:24:23,892 --> 01:24:27,195
to needs is contrary to the

1063
01:24:27,195 --> 01:24:31,132
divine scheme of creation
and to dignity of man.

1064
01:24:34,636 --> 01:24:40,341
However, there is another
aspect in the awareness of need.

1065
01:24:40,341 --> 01:24:45,613
It also warns man against
total gratification

1066
01:24:47,682 --> 01:24:49,017
of his needs.

1067
01:24:49,951 --> 01:24:51,453
Some needs,

1068
01:24:51,686 --> 01:24:59,260
and to our chagrin, the most pressing
ones, must and will never be gratified.

1069
01:24:59,928 --> 01:25:01,696
That's what Judaism says.

1070
01:25:01,696 --> 01:25:06,501
The awareness of need is
of a dialectical nature.

1071
01:25:06,501 --> 01:25:08,203
It has an inner contradiction.

1072
01:25:08,603 --> 01:25:12,540
There are two aspects which
are mutually exclusive.

1073
01:25:13,475 --> 01:25:16,077
One aspect is: gratify your needs.

1074
01:25:16,845 --> 01:25:20,849
Gratification is incumbent upon man.

1075
01:25:20,849 --> 01:25:23,651
It is incumbent upon man
to gratify his needs.

1076
01:25:24,352 --> 01:25:29,491
If man tries to suppress his
needs like monastic philosophy or

1077
01:25:29,491 --> 01:25:39,701
asceticism would recommend, then
he's actually lowering his dignity.

1078
01:25:40,435 --> 01:25:43,571
On the other hand, there's another aspect.

1079
01:25:43,905 --> 01:25:45,540
Total gratification.

1080
01:25:46,307 --> 01:25:48,710
To become an addict?

1081
01:25:49,344 --> 01:25:51,713
To become a voluptuary?

1082
01:25:52,814 --> 01:25:57,185
To gratify every need 
and totally gratify?

1083
01:25:59,287 --> 01:26:00,188
Forbidden.

1084
01:26:00,188 --> 01:26:01,422
It's forbidden.

1085
01:26:01,789 --> 01:26:03,191
You shouldn't do that.

1086
01:26:03,191 --> 01:26:04,559
Some needs

1087
01:26:04,559 --> 01:26:10,632
deserve to be gratified, some needs
should be suppressed or, rather,

1088
01:26:10,632 --> 01:26:14,702
excluded from the human "need" awareness.

1089
01:26:14,702 --> 01:26:18,306
Suppression is the word
which Judaism does not like.

1090
01:26:19,407 --> 01:26:24,879
The "need" awareness tells man

1091
01:26:26,281 --> 01:26:33,321
that total gratification will in the
long run, could in the long run, destroy

1092
01:26:33,321 --> 01:26:35,790
man's dignity and man's humanity.

1093
01:26:36,991 --> 01:26:40,061
What should man do in such a case?

1094
01:26:40,461 --> 01:26:42,597
What should he do?

1095
01:26:45,233 --> 01:26:48,169
He's caught in the
crucible of contradiction.

1096
01:26:49,904 --> 01:26:52,774
What advice should he follow?

1097
01:26:52,774 --> 01:27:02,617
Advice number one, gratification of
needs is a human performance and man

1098
01:27:03,585 --> 01:27:10,158
will enhance his dignity by gratifying
his needs, or should he listen and pay

1099
01:27:10,158 --> 01:27:13,228
attention to the advice to 
just the reverse?

1100
01:27:15,363 --> 01:27:19,867
Namely, total gratification
of needs is forbidden.

1101
01:27:20,468 --> 01:27:25,640
You will lose your human dignity
if you'll succumb to need.

1102
01:27:27,508 --> 01:27:33,982
Of course, Judaism comes forward
with a complete axiological

1103
01:27:33,982 --> 01:27:36,284
doctrine of human needs.

1104
01:27:36,884 --> 01:27:43,258
It tries to teach man which needs should
and which should not be gratified.

1105
01:27:44,092 --> 01:27:47,228
This is basically the essence of halachah.

1106
01:27:47,228 --> 01:27:48,129
You'll ask

1107
01:27:48,129 --> 01:27:54,569
me what halachah is recommending man,
the modus operandi, how man should relate

1108
01:27:54,569 --> 01:28:01,075
himself to both aspects of the "need"
awareness, to the aspect which recommends

1109
01:28:01,075 --> 01:28:08,416
gratification and to the aspect which
tells him total gratification is insane

1110
01:28:08,416 --> 01:28:10,918
and means destruction of the personality.

1111
01:28:11,786 --> 01:28:19,694
There are criteria by which one may be
guided in his attempt to treat his needs,

1112
01:28:19,694 --> 01:28:23,531
his "need" awareness on a selective basis.

1113
01:28:24,265 --> 01:28:26,367
The halachic prayer, it's hard for me

1114
01:28:26,367 --> 01:28:29,537
now – time is almost up.

1115
01:28:31,239 --> 01:28:35,209
You don't know how much time
I allocated to myself, huh?

1116
01:28:36,477 --> 01:28:38,413
I didn't ask you.

1117
01:28:44,986 --> 01:28:51,359
So, I could prove it to you by
studying each brachah separately.

1118
01:28:52,093 --> 01:28:56,998
For the brachos, for those
benedictions contain not only the

1119
01:28:56,998 --> 01:29:04,005
fact that man has needs but also
a scale, a hierarchy of needs.

1120
01:29:04,205 --> 01:29:09,177
Instructs man to distinguish
between worthwhile, constructive

1121
01:29:09,177 --> 01:29:11,212
gratification of need

1122
01:29:11,212 --> 01:29:14,982
and a disjunctive one.

1123
01:29:16,984 --> 01:29:22,557
It means that in addition to
the awareness of need, man

1124
01:29:22,557 --> 01:29:23,691
must what?

1125
01:29:24,459 --> 01:29:28,896
Must also possess the logos, I
mentioned before, the logos of need.

1126
01:29:29,864 --> 01:29:37,372
Man should not only be sensitive
to his needs but also know

1127
01:29:37,372 --> 01:29:39,574
and evaluate them as well.

1128
01:29:40,141 --> 01:29:44,545
He's supposed to relate them
to moral norms and their

1129
01:29:44,545 --> 01:29:48,716
gratification, thus ethicized.

1130
01:29:49,384 --> 01:29:53,454
There are no neutral 
activities in Judaism.

1131
01:29:53,921 --> 01:29:58,793
There is no division of sectors
into mundane and sacred.

1132
01:29:58,793 --> 01:30:04,565
Every sector in human life can either
serve as a sanctuary for God or

1133
01:30:04,565 --> 01:30:10,538
deteriorate into a madhouse of profanity
and absurdity, and it's up to man

1134
01:30:12,273 --> 01:30:13,808
to decide.

1135
01:30:15,042 --> 01:30:22,283
And the main decision, the most
important decision that man makes, is

1136
01:30:22,283 --> 01:30:28,156
concerned with the problem of
need, which needs be gratified

1137
01:30:28,156 --> 01:30:31,692
and which eliminated 
and disowned by man.

1138
01:30:33,227 --> 01:30:37,498
At this stage – and this is in
the Shemoneh Esrei – there is

1139
01:30:37,498 --> 01:30:42,136
a hierarchy of needs, beginning
with Atah Chonen and closing,

1140
01:30:42,136 --> 01:30:44,071
concluding with Shomei'a Tefillah.

1141
01:30:44,505 --> 01:30:51,179
At this stage, prayer is not
just a shriek, not just a cry,

1142
01:30:52,413 --> 01:30:55,149
and not just a howl anymore.

1143
01:30:55,750 --> 01:31:02,290
It is rather a well-defined
thought, a clear conception.

1144
01:31:02,890 --> 01:31:07,462
Therefore, at this stage, when
man introduces the logos of

1145
01:31:07,462 --> 01:31:10,731
needs, it turns into tefillah.

1146
01:31:10,731 --> 01:31:16,337
What the exact semantics of tefillah, of
the term tefillah is, we do not know.

1147
01:31:16,337 --> 01:31:17,738
It's very hard.

1148
01:31:17,738 --> 01:31:20,208
There are many opinions,
but one thing we do know.
